---
---
<section class="card hidden" data-step="sort-group">
  <div class="pill mb-3">Step 4: Group ranking</div>
  <h3 class="text-xl font-display">Rank this mini-set</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-latte-subtext1">
    Drag the titles into order. This gives the model a richer signal than a
    single A/B click.
  </p>
  <ul class="sortable-list" data-sortable-list></ul>
  <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-latte-subtext0" data-group-coverage>
    Coverage: 0 / 0 titles touched (0 remaining)
  </p>
  <p class="text-xs text-latte-subtext0" data-group-estimate>
    Baseline target: ~0 group sorts (~2x touches).
  </p>
  <p class="text-xs text-latte-subtext0">
    You can stop early, but fewer group sorts make the ordering rougher. Use
    uncertainty analysis or switch to pairwise refine for more stability.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <button class="btn" type="button" data-action="submit-sort">
      Submit ranking
    </button>
    <button class="btn-secondary" type="button" data-action="skip-sort">
      Skip for now
    </button>
    <button
      class="btn-secondary hidden"
      type="button"
      data-action="switch-to-pairwise"
    >
      Switch to pairwise refine
    </button>
  </div>
</section>
